1
00:04:26,232 --> 00:04:28,166
May I help you?

2
00:04:54,394 --> 00:04:58,194
A friend of ours would like
to speak to you this evening.

3
00:05:06,739 --> 00:05:08,730
I just shine shoes.

4
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:11,003
There'll be shoes there.

5
00:06:04,130 --> 00:06:07,156
Two weeks ago, a man named Aaronberg
was shot to death...

6
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:10,168
the corner of Racine and Belden.

7
00:06:10,236 --> 00:06:12,466
This is public knowledge.

8
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:16,065
Two people saw the crime,
and this was also in the papers.

9
00:06:16,142 --> 00:06:19,168
This is public knowledge.

10
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:22,772
What I am going to tell you now
is not public knowledge.

11
00:06:22,849 --> 00:06:24,817
Do you understand?

12
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:32,180
Good. The act was committed
by a person unknown...

13
00:06:32,258 --> 00:06:34,988
a man in a gray overcoat.

14
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:38,462
Unfortunately, a friend of ours
has been mistakenly identified...

15
00:06:38,531 --> 00:06:40,192
as the man who did the murder.

16
00:06:40,266 --> 00:06:41,665
Show him the picture.

17
00:06:49,308 --> 00:06:52,402
This is the man who has been
mistakenly accused.

18
00:07:04,123 --> 00:07:05,681
Do you understand?

19
00:07:10,363 --> 00:07:13,332
To prevent a grave injustice
from being done...

20
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:15,833
to protect an innocent man...

21
00:07:15,902 --> 00:07:18,336
someone must confess
to the crime...

22
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:20,372
someone who looks like...

23
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,509
This person would plead guilty
to murder...

24
00:07:24,577 --> 00:07:28,809
and would unfortunately spend a term
of three to five years in prison.

25
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:39,220
To such a person,
we are prepared to pay...

26
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:44,152
this amount of money
per year...

27
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:46,960
for each year he spent
in prison.

28
00:07:47,033 --> 00:07:49,661
You could say
you were in prison now.

29
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:53,931
You must have a dream.
Do you have a dream?

30
00:07:57,777 --> 00:08:00,041
What is that dream?

31
00:08:04,550 --> 00:08:06,313
A boat.

32
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:07,977
A boat.

33
00:08:08,054 --> 00:08:10,045
A fishing boat.

34
00:08:10,122 --> 00:08:13,387
Your dream is a fishing boat?

35
00:08:13,459 --> 00:08:15,757
In Sicily.

36
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:18,353
In three years...

37
00:08:18,431 --> 00:08:20,661
you could have that fishing boat.

38
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:23,531
You could earn yourself
that boat.

39
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:25,867
If you stay in your shoe store...

40
00:08:25,938 --> 00:08:29,135
what will you have in three years?

41
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:31,438
What will you have in three years?

42
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:34,746
What do you have now?

43
00:08:42,088 --> 00:08:44,283
Will you do it for me?

44
00:08:58,104 --> 00:09:00,572
You've just made a grave mistake.

45
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:03,234
All right.

46
00:09:03,309 --> 00:09:05,140
Shine 'em up, Joe.

47
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:10,841
Get me Marty in Detroit. Tell him
I want to see him as soon as possible.

48
00:09:10,917 --> 00:09:13,681
- And get me whats-his-name downtown.
- Yes, sir.

49
00:09:13,753 --> 00:09:16,483
Watch out for the socks.
These are cashmere socks.

50
00:09:19,258 --> 00:09:20,850
Yes.

51
00:09:29,101 --> 00:09:32,093
Mr. Silver, get me downtown...

52
00:09:32,171 --> 00:09:34,298
and tell them I need a guy
for that project...

53
00:09:34,373 --> 00:09:36,102
we were discussing.

54
00:09:36,175 --> 00:09:39,667
- He'll know what I mean.
- Yes, sir.

55
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:41,679
Come on, boy.

56
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:44,307
We want to get you back
to your shoe shine stand.

57
00:09:44,383 --> 00:09:46,510
Yes, this is Mr. Silver
in Chicago.

58
00:09:51,023 --> 00:09:52,650
That's right.

59
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:57,623
No, I have the number on his boat,
but I was told I could find him here.

60
00:09:57,697 --> 00:09:59,961
I'll hold.

61
00:10:00,032 --> 00:10:02,057
A man comes into my house,
what does he want?

62
00:10:02,134 --> 00:10:04,864
I tell him, "Whatever you want."
A fellow's dying.

63
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:06,905
Fifty bucks a week, says,
"Buy me a boat."

64
00:10:06,973 --> 00:10:09,965
Fine.
I'll buy him a pushcart.

65
00:10:10,042 --> 00:10:13,569
Buy him an organ with a monkey,
and he can put a bandana on his head.

66
00:10:15,247 --> 00:10:18,614
Son of a bitch immigrant said
he wanted a boat. I'll give him a boat.

67
00:10:21,153 --> 00:10:23,383
I do it.

68
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,924
Just a minute.

69
00:10:30,229 --> 00:10:32,288
It won't be necessary.

70
00:10:33,899 --> 00:10:35,696
Thank you.

71
00:10:39,171 --> 00:10:42,470
This is a Sicilian coin.

72
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:45,032
- The Sicilian people say...
- Mr. Green.

73
00:10:45,111 --> 00:10:47,079
- "A big man..."
- Excuse me.

74
00:10:49,548 --> 00:10:52,915
"A big man knows the value
of a small coin."

75
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:55,783
My friendship is a small coin...

76
00:10:55,855 --> 00:10:58,255
but it is all I have
to offer you.

77
00:11:02,294 --> 00:11:03,522
Thank you.

78
00:11:09,902 --> 00:11:11,836
The papers, please.

79
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:19,940
Sign here.

80
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:22,503
This is your confession.

81
00:11:30,322 --> 00:11:32,313
Good. And now...

82
00:11:45,137 --> 00:11:47,264
We need your fingerprints.

83
00:11:47,339 --> 00:11:49,603
Pick up the gun and close it.

84
00:12:05,524 --> 00:12:07,492
To my new friend.

85
00:12:34,787 --> 00:12:37,517
- You done good on that thing.
- Thanks, Frank.

86
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:40,058
Marcotti. What, are you
gettin' ambitious?

87
00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:42,151
- Just doin' a job.
- Willie.

88
00:12:42,228 --> 00:12:43,991
- Thanks, Frank.
- Guys.

89
00:12:44,063 --> 00:12:45,690
Thank you.

90
00:12:45,765 --> 00:12:48,290
Jerry, we got a...
What is this?

91
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:51,734
Jerry somethin'-or-other works here?
I thought we sent him to the farm team.

92
00:12:51,804 --> 00:12:55,137
- Why's that, Frank?
- Seems he can't follow orders.

93
00:12:55,207 --> 00:12:58,074
Can't follow orders?
Is the guy a team player or what?

94
00:12:58,144 --> 00:13:01,170
- No, it would seem not.
- That's a shame, Frank.

95
00:13:01,247 --> 00:13:05,013
- Yes, I agree.
- No pain, no pals, no prospects.

96
00:13:05,084 --> 00:13:09,111
- What kind of guy is that?
- A word to the wise is sufficient.

97
00:13:09,188 --> 00:13:12,715
What's happening on the South Side.
Lead off with the shipping thing.

98
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,726
Here are the figures
on the shipping.

99
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:18,525
Glad to hear from you too, Jerry.
Maybe when you get off probation...

100
00:13:18,597 --> 00:13:20,531
Do you think
you can get this clean?

101
00:13:20,599 --> 00:13:23,227
What does a guy get
who can't toe the line?

102
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:26,362
- Probation.
- Right.

103
00:13:29,575 --> 00:13:31,099
Frankie.

104
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:36,514
- What's up?
- I have a little errand for you.

105
00:13:36,582 --> 00:13:39,676
I want you to get the right guy
for this and take care of it for me.

106
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:55,900
Hey, Cinderella.

107
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,936
Come here.

108
00:14:45,951 --> 00:14:48,181
Come here.
I want you to get me in the area.

109
00:14:48,254 --> 00:14:50,688
Jerry's gonna handle it.
He's a very good man.

110
00:14:50,756 --> 00:14:54,055
- What did you tell him?
- To stick to this guy the whole weekend.

111
00:14:54,126 --> 00:14:56,492
- He won't let him out of his sight.
- Don't screw this up.

112
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:58,587
He's good.
He'll handle it.

113
00:15:24,156 --> 00:15:25,953
Mr. Green?

114
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:28,118
All right.
Listen and learn something.

115
00:15:30,362 --> 00:15:32,489
- Now you do this one right.
- I'm doin' it right.

116
00:15:32,564 --> 00:15:34,429
I'm gettin' off probation.

117
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,798
Just do this,
and then we'll see.

118
00:16:07,766 --> 00:16:09,529
Why did you kill him?

119
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:12,001
He was a no-good son of a bitch.

120
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:15,040
And?

121
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:17,098
- He...
- You owed him money.

122
00:16:17,176 --> 00:16:21,408
Yeah, yeah.
Owe him some money.

123
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:25,541
- How much did you owe him?
- Fifteen hundred dollars.

124
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:27,312
That's right.

125
00:16:27,386 --> 00:16:29,411
What did you do with the money?

126
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:31,718
I lose it at the racetrack.

127
00:16:35,227 --> 00:16:38,856
What time was it you killed him?
Hold it. You know that one.

128
00:16:38,931 --> 00:16:41,399
How many times did you shoot him?

129
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:43,401
Three times.

130
00:16:43,469 --> 00:16:46,233
Don't get it too pat.
Three or four.

131
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:48,466
I shoot him three or four times.

132
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:51,270
Son of a bitch.

133
00:16:53,078 --> 00:16:55,137
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

134
00:16:55,214 --> 00:16:57,148
You're a natural.

135
00:16:57,216 --> 00:16:59,275
You got the thing cold.

136
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:10,488
We're not gonna do no more?

137
00:17:10,562 --> 00:17:12,928
No, you know it.

138
00:17:12,998 --> 00:17:15,125
You know it.

139
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:21,831
Hey, this is ridiculous.

140
00:17:21,907 --> 00:17:25,365
You're goin' to jail for three years.

141
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:27,105
What do you want to do?

142
00:17:27,179 --> 00:17:29,374
We'll do something, huh?

143
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:32,475
What?

144
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:34,280
What do you...

145
00:17:34,353 --> 00:17:36,617
Want to get a couple of broads?

146
00:17:36,688 --> 00:17:39,782
- Do you want to see a show?
- No.

147
00:17:39,858 --> 00:17:42,884
Hey, I'll get you tickets
to something.

148
00:17:42,961 --> 00:17:45,452
They're telling me
I should not leave this room.

149
00:17:45,531 --> 00:17:47,123
They?

150
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:52,364
There is no "they."
I am "they."

151
00:17:52,438 --> 00:17:54,929
What do you want to do?

152
00:17:55,007 --> 00:17:56,907
Can we...

153
00:17:56,975 --> 00:17:59,603
Can we take a walk
down by the beach?

154
00:17:59,678 --> 00:18:01,976
It'd be okay?

155
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:06,345
Okay?

156
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:12,223
I'll show you what's okay.

157
00:18:32,244 --> 00:18:34,178
Have a nice day.

158
00:18:35,314 --> 00:18:37,248
Take care, now.

159
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:53,221
- You like to travel?
- Sure.

160
00:18:53,298 --> 00:18:56,267
- Okay, good.
- I like.

161
00:18:56,335 --> 00:18:57,927
Good.

162
00:18:59,738 --> 00:19:01,706
Glad to hear it.
Here to make you happy.

163
00:19:01,773 --> 00:19:03,866
Anything to please.
That's me.

164
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,446
Two days, understand?

165
00:19:08,514 --> 00:19:11,005
A little fun, a little memory,
then back to Chicago.

166
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:13,881
Back to Chicago. I shoot
the son of a bitch in the heart.

167
00:19:13,952 --> 00:19:16,546
When I say it, out here,
do it.

168
00:19:16,622 --> 00:19:19,090
- You the boss.
- I am the boss.

169
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:21,649
You keep that clear,
we're gonna get on fine.

170
00:19:49,721 --> 00:19:53,487
Hey, how you doin'?
What are you doin' here?

171
00:19:53,559 --> 00:19:56,619
How are you? I'm doin' fine.
How should I be doin'?

172
00:19:56,695 --> 00:19:59,493
You know. Heard you mucked up
back there last month.

173
00:19:59,565 --> 00:20:02,033
- What does that mean?
- Heard they slapped your wrists.

174
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:04,500
- What wrists?
- Heard you had to stay after school.

175
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:06,162
Couldn't obey orders.

176
00:20:07,239 --> 00:20:08,831
Stay after school?

177
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:16,240
Are you joking me? Does this look
like staying after school?

178
00:20:22,421 --> 00:20:24,480
Who is he?

179
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:27,582
If you don't know,
then maybe you shouldn't know.

180
00:20:30,429 --> 00:20:33,330
- Are you staying at the hotel?
- Yeah, we're staying at the hotel.

181
00:20:33,398 --> 00:20:36,993
- Someone picking you up?
- I think they're sending someone down...

182
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:38,661
Get in the car.

183
00:21:09,234 --> 00:21:12,635
Hey, you know, I heard you got
in some deep powder back there.

184
00:21:12,704 --> 00:21:15,195
I heard they put you on probation.

185
00:21:15,274 --> 00:21:17,742
You can't believe
everything you hear.

186
00:21:17,809 --> 00:21:20,676
Sometimes they put out
a story, you know.

187
00:21:20,746 --> 00:21:22,941
And so you're...

188
00:21:23,015 --> 00:21:25,506
What, so you're...

189
00:21:25,584 --> 00:21:27,950
What I am is what you see.

190
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:32,955
And so your guy,
he's big back there.

191
00:21:34,026 --> 00:21:36,756
Babe, this is the guy...

192
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:40,457
behind the guy behind the guy.

193
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:45,365
But what I got to tell you is...

194
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:48,272
I cannot talk about it.

195
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:51,207
- I understand.
- He wants to have a quiet weekend.

196
00:21:51,276 --> 00:21:54,211
- I understand.
- But of this, bit of that. No fuss.

197
00:22:34,619 --> 00:22:36,951
- Billy. Thanks, pal.
- I'll walk you in.

198
00:22:40,258 --> 00:22:42,658
- Thanks, pal. I'll take it from here.
- No problem.

199
00:22:42,728 --> 00:22:44,320
Hey.

200
00:22:46,064 --> 00:22:48,760
Right this way.

201
00:22:50,502 --> 00:22:52,993
I'm trying to keep a low profile
here, you understand?

202
00:22:53,071 --> 00:22:56,336
- We like to go in quiet.
- Could we get some attention here?

203
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:06,841
May I help you?

204
00:23:09,287 --> 00:23:12,415
Yes. I'll have to get
right back to you.

205
00:23:12,491 --> 00:23:14,925
Good morning, gentlemen.
How good to have you with us.

206
00:23:14,993 --> 00:23:16,961
Shall we go up to the room?

207
00:23:36,348 --> 00:23:38,111
We're going upstairs.

208
00:23:38,183 --> 00:23:40,174
We'll be going to the Criterion Floor.

209
00:23:40,952 --> 00:23:42,977
Welcome to the Galaxy, gentlemen.

210
00:23:43,989 --> 00:23:46,719
- Tell them our guests are coming.
- Yes, sir.

211
00:23:49,561 --> 00:23:52,962
Anything you might need in Lake Tahoe,
sir, I'd be honored if you'd ask for me.

212
00:23:53,031 --> 00:23:54,623
Billy Drake.

213
00:23:57,636 --> 00:23:59,536
- Who is he?
- From Chicago.

214
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:01,731
Yes, sir.

215
00:24:01,807 --> 00:24:03,206
I understand.

216
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:05,334
Absolutely.

217
00:24:05,410 --> 00:24:07,878
I understand.
Yes, sir.

218
00:24:07,946 --> 00:24:10,073
I understand completely.

219
00:24:10,148 --> 00:24:11,672
Ah, here they are now.

220
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:15,544
Hi.

221
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:21,418
Welcome to
the Criterion Floor, Mr...

222
00:24:21,493 --> 00:24:22,983
Johnson.

223
00:24:23,061 --> 00:24:25,552
Look, it's a good idea...

224
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:29,794
It's very important that nobody know
that Mr. Johnson is here.

225
00:24:29,868 --> 00:24:33,201
I understand. I am your butler.
My name is Randy.

226
00:24:33,271 --> 00:24:36,604
And I'll be at your disposal
24 hours a day.

227
00:24:44,583 --> 00:24:48,280
See to the bedrooms, if you would.
And turn on the music, please.

228
00:24:52,057 --> 00:24:55,720
Any help with travel arrangements,
special dietary preparation...

229
00:24:55,794 --> 00:24:58,285
cleaning, mending,
shoe shine, shopping...

230
00:24:58,363 --> 00:25:01,594
or any other aid that you require,
don't hesitate to ring.

231
00:25:01,666 --> 00:25:04,760
The manager has informed me
that all the staff have been advised...

232
00:25:04,836 --> 00:25:07,361
that any wish expressed by you
or Mr. Johnson...

233
00:25:07,439 --> 00:25:10,738
No, no, no. Nobody is to know
that Mr. Johnson is here.

234
00:25:10,809 --> 00:25:13,334
Believe me, I understand.

235
00:25:13,411 --> 00:25:15,345
Your privacy will be respected.

236
00:25:15,413 --> 00:25:18,905
We're here for two days' quiet.
A little low-profile relaxation.

237
00:25:18,984 --> 00:25:20,747
I completely understand.

238
00:25:20,819 --> 00:25:23,481
We at the Galaxy understand
and appreciate your position.

239
00:25:23,555 --> 00:25:25,489
Believe me.

240
00:25:25,557 --> 00:25:28,458
The Criterion Floor in concept
and execution exists only...

241
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:30,620
to cater to your special needs.

242
00:25:41,973 --> 00:25:45,306
Secretarial or legal services.
I am a notary, should you require it.

243
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:47,311
Where are the bags?

244
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:49,939
We lost our bags
on a connection.

245
00:25:50,015 --> 00:25:52,415
Our stores and shops are yours.
Whatever you require...

246
00:25:52,484 --> 00:25:54,418
go down or ring
and they'll have it sent up.

247
00:25:54,486 --> 00:25:56,954
- That's very kind of you, but...
- Credit in the casino.

248
00:25:57,022 --> 00:25:59,456
Whatever you require
in financial services.

249
00:25:59,524 --> 00:26:03,051
We have a 24-hour access
to a ticker tape of the major markets.

250
00:26:07,065 --> 00:26:08,327
Allow me.

251
00:26:16,908 --> 00:26:20,469
Tickets to the show, Jackie Shore,
tonight in the Constellation Room...

252
00:26:20,545 --> 00:26:22,945
or tickets for
any other show in town.

253
00:26:23,014 --> 00:26:25,608
The sights and sounds of Lake Tahoe.

254
00:26:25,684 --> 00:26:28,949
And here's my card. I'm at that number
or they'll beep me there...

255
00:26:29,020 --> 00:26:31,750
at any time, any time at all.

256
00:26:31,823 --> 00:26:35,589
Oh, Mr. Johnson,
any questions about the room?

257
00:26:35,660 --> 00:26:38,527
I believe we have anticipated
your tobacco requirements...

258
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:41,657
but if there's anything we've left out,
don't hesitate to let me know.

259
00:26:59,484 --> 00:27:02,351
It is a pleasure and an honor
having you as a guest of the Galaxy...

260
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:04,115
and of the Criterion Floor.

261
00:27:04,189 --> 00:27:07,317
My name is Randy, and whatever I can do
to make your stay more enjoyable...

262
00:27:07,392 --> 00:27:09,792
it will be my honor
and pleasure to serve you.

263
00:27:09,861 --> 00:27:12,694
The concierge desk and our kitchen
are at your disposal...

264
00:27:12,764 --> 00:27:15,130
and should you wish to shop,
our shops and stores...

265
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,397
are open to you on a private basis
24 hours a day.

266
00:27:18,470 --> 00:27:22,497
And whatever services you should desire,
there is, of course, no bill.

267
00:27:22,574 --> 00:27:24,872
Your money's no good in this hotel.

268
00:27:38,156 --> 00:27:39,851
Mr. Johnson...

269
00:27:39,924 --> 00:27:42,119
you have beautiful hands.

270
00:27:42,193 --> 00:27:45,890
Yes, and a lovely treatment
of the hands, if I may say so, sir.

271
00:27:45,964 --> 00:27:49,730
An excellent choice.
Clean without being austere.

272
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:01,001
Mr. Johnson, it's been a pleasure.

273
00:28:06,985 --> 00:28:09,476
It's always a pleasure to clothe
a man of your physique.

274
00:28:09,554 --> 00:28:11,818
You honor it, sir,
with your custom.

275
00:28:22,834 --> 00:28:24,768
Yes, yes, yes.

276
00:28:24,836 --> 00:28:26,895
Okay.
Wanna pass, huh?

277
00:28:26,971 --> 00:28:29,496
Clothes don't make the man.
I make the man.

278
00:28:29,574 --> 00:28:32,099
You understand me?
Just because we got new clothes...

279
00:28:32,177 --> 00:28:34,441
- Something to drink, gentlemen?
- Scotch, please.

280
00:28:34,512 --> 00:28:37,345
Nothing for me.
I'm here to gamble.

281
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,712
Here we go.

282
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:52,324
Give me 5 on the 9, 5 on the 19,
