311
00:30:20,518 --> 00:30:22,452
And if there's anything at all
that I can do for you...

312
00:30:22,520 --> 00:30:24,647
- Thanks.
- I'll tell you, Jerry...

313
00:30:24,722 --> 00:30:26,747
I never win nothing.

314
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:29,419
- Maybe we can fix that.
- Jerry.

315
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:32,292
Not even you can fix
something like this.

316
00:30:32,363 --> 00:30:35,093
- Not even me, huh?
- Not even you.

317
00:30:35,166 --> 00:30:37,691
Not even someone like me?

318
00:30:37,769 --> 00:30:39,236
Put it in.

319
00:30:42,607 --> 00:30:44,541
Hey, wait a second!

320
00:30:46,377 --> 00:30:48,368
There is something
you could do for me.

321
00:30:48,446 --> 00:30:51,381
I'd like to give Mr. Johnson
a little treat.

322
00:30:51,449 --> 00:30:54,111
- Absolutely, sir.
- Could we arrange for him...

323
00:30:54,185 --> 00:30:56,881
as a lark,
to win a little, you know?

324
00:30:56,955 --> 00:30:58,388
- To win?
- Just a little.

325
00:30:58,456 --> 00:31:00,720
- To win at the casino.
- Just a little... $50, $100.

326
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:04,387
As a thrill, you know?
Can you do that?

327
00:31:04,462 --> 00:31:07,158
- Well...
- Whatever it is, I'll make it up.

328
00:31:07,232 --> 00:31:09,928
- You're saying you'll pay it back?
- That's what I'm saying.

329
00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:50,506
Broke so soon?

330
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:53,635
The slots are cold.
Let's try something else.

331
00:31:55,046 --> 00:31:56,638
Twelve.

332
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:06,917
Twelve.

333
00:32:08,826 --> 00:32:11,306
- This table open?
- Yes, sir, it is.

334
00:32:11,362 --> 00:32:14,024
Okay. You got black, you got red,
you got numbers.

335
00:32:14,098 --> 00:32:16,498
- What do you want to bet?
- I'll take black.

336
00:32:16,567 --> 00:32:20,162
Take a number. Pick a number.

337
00:32:20,238 --> 00:32:23,264
You pick a number, it hits,
it pays 35 to 1.

338
00:32:23,341 --> 00:32:25,309
Put five bucks on a number.

339
00:32:25,376 --> 00:32:28,004
- We're partners.
- No, it's yours.

340
00:32:28,079 --> 00:32:31,446
We're partners.
Whatever happens, we're 50/50, okay?

341
00:32:31,516 --> 00:32:33,143
- Yeah, okay.
- Okay.

342
00:32:33,217 --> 00:32:36,277
You know what number
I always play?

343
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:39,915
My flight number.
What flight did we come in on?

344
00:32:39,991 --> 00:32:42,425
- Twelve, wasn't it?
- Yeah, yeah.

345
00:32:42,493 --> 00:32:44,757
I think you're right.
I think it was number 12.

346
00:32:50,168 --> 00:32:51,863
- I got to talk to you.
- Not now.

347
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:00,436
Twelve.
The number is twelve.

348
00:33:00,511 --> 00:33:01,842
- I win.
- Yes, sir.

349
00:33:03,614 --> 00:33:05,809
Did you see what my friend did?

350
00:33:05,883 --> 00:33:07,817
Bravo, Mr. Johnson. Good play.

351
00:33:07,885 --> 00:33:10,410
We got to lose the lighting guy.
He's napping up there.

352
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:12,752
I'm not saying it's hurting
the show. It's not.

353
00:33:12,824 --> 00:33:14,451
Have you seen the show?

354
00:33:14,525 --> 00:33:17,323
- Have you seen the show, Mr...
- And here's your winnings, sir.

355
00:33:17,395 --> 00:33:20,853
- Have you seen the show?
- No, I can't say that I have.

356
00:33:20,932 --> 00:33:23,400
What do you mean, you haven't seen it?
How long have you been here?

357
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:24,696
Place your bets.

358
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:31,373
One thousand dollars
on number 12.

359
00:33:31,442 --> 00:33:34,343
- There's a bit I do, working the crowd.
- This is not the time, Jackie.

360
00:33:34,412 --> 00:33:37,313
I want to make a point here.
You've got a beautiful, fine show...

361
00:33:37,382 --> 00:33:39,316
well thought-out,
but if you don't have the support...

362
00:33:39,384 --> 00:33:42,353
- This is my theme: Support.
- Twelve again.

363
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:44,547
I win again!

364
00:33:44,622 --> 00:33:46,749
Yes, sir, you did.

365
00:33:52,964 --> 00:33:54,761
How much we win?

366
00:33:56,901 --> 00:33:59,495
Thirty-five thousand dollars.

367
00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:07,609
We fly number 12,
we play number 12.

368
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:10,877
That's a lot of money.

369
00:34:10,948 --> 00:34:14,042
What number do you want
to play now?

370
00:34:16,087 --> 00:34:18,112
That's enough.

371
00:34:20,725 --> 00:34:23,023
Come on.
I'll buy you a car.

372
00:34:23,094 --> 00:34:26,325
- Sir...
- Yeah, hold on a second.

373
00:34:32,703 --> 00:34:35,638
- What's happening?
- That guy just won a couple bucks.

374
00:34:35,706 --> 00:34:38,106
Hey, what we do with this money?

375
00:34:38,176 --> 00:34:41,339
Gino, we got to give it back.

376
00:34:42,513 --> 00:34:45,243
Why?
I win this.

377
00:34:45,316 --> 00:34:47,181
Yeah, but...

378
00:34:47,251 --> 00:34:50,049
- I win this money.
- Yeah, but listen, listen.

379
00:34:50,121 --> 00:34:53,955
It's a thing of hospitality.

380
00:34:54,025 --> 00:34:57,825
We're...
We're guests in their hotel.

381
00:34:57,895 --> 00:35:00,022
Sure, we could take the money.

382
00:35:00,098 --> 00:35:02,692
It's not a question of the money.

383
00:35:02,767 --> 00:35:05,634
It's just for the sake of...

384
00:35:06,871 --> 00:35:09,066
honor.

385
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:11,506
To be an honorable guest.

386
00:35:11,576 --> 00:35:14,067
It's not the money?

387
00:35:14,145 --> 00:35:16,807
It's honor?

388
00:35:18,616 --> 00:35:20,345
Would you move back, please?

389
00:35:20,418 --> 00:35:23,546
- What happened?
- That guy just won 35 grand.

390
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:28,224
Excuse me, sir.
I have to talk to you.

391
00:35:28,292 --> 00:35:31,693
- In a minute.
- I have to talk to you.

392
00:35:35,900 --> 00:35:37,697
How this game work?

393
00:35:37,768 --> 00:35:39,633
Well, we pay a hundred to one.

394
00:35:39,704 --> 00:35:42,400
What that means is, if you bet a dollar
and your number wins...

395
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:44,407
you win $100.

396
00:35:44,475 --> 00:35:47,808
- How much I can bet?
- Just as advertised, sir...

397
00:35:47,879 --> 00:35:50,177
the Wheel of Fortune,
the pride of the Galaxy...

398
00:35:50,248 --> 00:35:52,910
never refused a bet
of any size.

399
00:35:52,984 --> 00:35:56,215
If I bet $35,000, how much I win?

400
00:35:56,287 --> 00:35:58,551
If you bet $35,000...

401
00:35:58,623 --> 00:36:02,457
you'd win $3,500,000.

402
00:36:03,594 --> 00:36:06,290
I bet $35,000.

403
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,093
Put on number 12.

404
00:36:11,936 --> 00:36:15,736
Thirty-five thousand dollars
on number 12.

405
00:36:15,806 --> 00:36:18,240
Do me a favor, honey.
Put $1,000 on number 12.

406
00:36:18,309 --> 00:36:22,177
A hundred on 1, a hundred on 2,
500 on 12 and a hundred on 21.

407
00:36:22,246 --> 00:36:24,373
- Lord hates a coward.
- Bet for me.

408
00:36:24,448 --> 00:36:26,643
- Five hundred on twelve.
- Twenty on 12.

409
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:31,719
- Another 50.
- Thank you, and bets are closed.

410
00:36:31,789 --> 00:36:33,723
- One dollar on 12.
- All right. Thank you.

411
00:36:33,791 --> 00:36:36,157
And bets are closed.

412
00:36:40,565 --> 00:36:43,261
And round and round she goes.

413
00:36:43,334 --> 00:36:46,565
Where she stops, nobody knows.
Good luck to you all.

414
00:36:46,637 --> 00:36:50,300
- Please, please.
- Come on, baby. Come home to Papa.

415
00:36:54,245 --> 00:36:57,078
One time, baby. This is it.

416
00:36:57,148 --> 00:36:59,776
Come to Papa, baby. Come on.

417
00:37:05,823 --> 00:37:08,986
And the number is...

418
00:37:19,003 --> 00:37:20,630
seventy-four.

419
00:37:20,705 --> 00:37:23,037
The number is 74.
I'm sorry.

420
00:37:23,107 --> 00:37:26,372
The number is 74.
No winners on 74.

421
00:37:26,444 --> 00:37:29,311
No winners.
No winners on 74.

422
00:37:35,786 --> 00:37:37,811
Hell of a bet, son.

423
00:37:39,624 --> 00:37:42,525
I'm sorry you lost
all that money, sir.

424
00:37:44,996 --> 00:37:46,657
Things change.

425
00:37:53,904 --> 00:37:56,338
Your drink, sir.

426
00:38:00,177 --> 00:38:01,872
Thank you.

427
00:38:22,333 --> 00:38:25,393
I'll tell you what's crazy, folks.
The longer I'm married...

428
00:38:25,469 --> 00:38:27,801
the more I'm losing
my single instincts.

429
00:38:27,872 --> 00:38:30,841
I was at a party in Hollywood...
big show business party...

430
00:38:30,908 --> 00:38:32,842
beautiful blonde starlet
comes up to me.

431
00:38:32,910 --> 00:38:35,674
She says, " My husband's away
for the weekend. How about a lift home?"

432
00:38:35,746 --> 00:38:38,874
I said, "If you knew he would be away,
you should've made travel arrangements."

433
00:38:41,385 --> 00:38:43,319
I have a theory criminals want
to get caught.

434
00:38:43,387 --> 00:38:46,618
The <i>Reporter</i> said 18 of the 20
suspects arrested are known...

435
00:38:46,691 --> 00:38:48,659
to have organized crime ties.

436
00:38:48,726 --> 00:38:51,991
If they don't want to get caught, don't
wear the ties. See what I'm saying?

437
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:08,804
- How's your drink?
- Good. Good.

438
00:39:18,422 --> 00:39:21,118
You handled yourself
very graciously back there.

439
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:25,629
When you are in Rome,
you do like the Romans do.

440
00:39:31,035 --> 00:39:33,333
I saw a guy today down at the tables.

441
00:39:33,404 --> 00:39:37,841
Shoots 35 grand in one roll,
craps out. He says, "Things change."

442
00:39:37,908 --> 00:39:41,241
And one thing that does not change,
ladies and gentlemen, is friendship.

443
00:39:41,312 --> 00:39:44,406
And I want to say hi to a good friend
of ours from Chicago, Mr. Johnson.

444
00:39:44,482 --> 00:39:48,350
Would you please stand up, Mr. Johnson?
Ladies and gentlemen, let him know.

445
00:39:48,419 --> 00:39:51,411
Mr. Johnson?
Mr. Johnson?

446
00:39:56,026 --> 00:39:58,586
Come on, folks. Give it up.
Give it up!

447
00:39:58,662 --> 00:40:02,655
Mr. Johnson. Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. Johnson from Chicago.

448
00:40:03,334 --> 00:40:05,734
Give it up one time
for Mr. Johnson.

449
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:09,000
Folks, take it from a man who knows,
there is nothing like friendship.

450
00:40:09,073 --> 00:40:12,099
'Cause if there was,
somebody would have invented it already.

451
00:40:12,176 --> 00:40:15,077
- Check five and thirteen, please.
- <i>One minute to curtain.</i>

452
00:40:15,146 --> 00:40:18,047
- Hey, have you got a minute?
- <i>Stop me if you got a problem.</i>

453
00:40:18,115 --> 00:40:21,949
Why am I getting this again?
I walked out of my light.

454
00:40:22,019 --> 00:40:23,987
- What is your guy doing up there?
- I can't talk about this now.

455
00:40:24,054 --> 00:40:26,750
Your lighting guy,
what is this, your wife's cousin?

456
00:40:26,824 --> 00:40:28,758
Now it's Jackie. Great.
What?

457
00:40:28,826 --> 00:40:32,091
Did I do something to you
in a previous life? What is this?

458
00:40:32,163 --> 00:40:35,724
- <i>Roger, microphone check.</i>
- Hey, Mr. Johnson!

459
00:40:38,235 --> 00:40:40,965
- Mr. Johnson, what a nice surprise.
- Yeah, very surprised.

460
00:40:41,038 --> 00:40:44,132
I hope you guys enjoyed the show,
and good of you to play along.

461
00:40:44,208 --> 00:40:47,837
Really very supportive, and I
appreciate that. You looked great.

462
00:40:47,912 --> 00:40:50,972
I thought I told you I didn't want any
publicity. We don't want any notice.

463
00:40:51,048 --> 00:40:53,346
<i>Thirty seconds to curtain, please.</i>

464
00:40:53,417 --> 00:40:56,853
Hey, guys, look, if I jumped wrong...
if you don't want any notice.

465
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:58,821
Yeah, bear with me here.

466
00:40:58,889 --> 00:41:02,188
- <i>On your cue, go black.</i>
- On stage, please.

467
00:41:03,494 --> 00:41:05,894
Maybe a little notice.
Cherry, Grace!

468
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:09,694
- <i>This is curtain, ladies and gentlemen.</i>
- I'd like you to meet Mr. Johnson.

469
00:41:09,767 --> 00:41:11,701
- <i>And now...</i>
- Let's go, girls.

470
00:41:11,769 --> 00:41:15,432
<i>The one, the only, the greatest revue</i>
<i>in the great state of Nevada...</i>

471
00:41:15,506 --> 00:41:18,839
<i>ladies and gentlemen, the Galaxy Hotel</i>
<i>is proud to present...</i>

472
00:41:18,909 --> 00:41:21,400
<i>the Fertile Crescent.</i>

473
00:41:35,659 --> 00:41:37,820
Do you mind if we come in?

474
00:41:51,308 --> 00:41:55,335
I always wondered
where I was meant to be.

475
00:41:55,412 --> 00:42:00,008
It's good to work, Jerry,
but it is also good to play.

476
00:42:04,488 --> 00:42:07,252
"The Ant and the Grasshopper."

477
00:42:08,926 --> 00:42:13,795
Once upon a time, there was
an ant and a grasshopper.

478
00:42:13,864 --> 00:42:17,630
All summer long,
the ant worked hard.

479
00:42:17,701 --> 00:42:21,364
The grasshopper,
he played the violin.

480
00:42:21,438 --> 00:42:23,372
He dance.

481
00:42:24,408 --> 00:42:25,670
Winter come.

482
00:42:26,410 --> 00:42:28,810
The ant grow fat.

483
00:42:28,879 --> 00:42:32,144
The grasshopper is cold.

484
00:42:33,651 --> 00:42:37,644
The grasshopper
eat the ant.

485
00:42:56,273 --> 00:42:58,298
Return to me.

486
00:43:03,213 --> 00:43:05,147
My darling, I adore you.

487
00:43:06,951 --> 00:43:08,885
