01:30:55,416 --> 01:30:57,782
What do you think the thing is,
sitting in a hotel three days...

965
01:30:57,852 --> 01:31:00,377
order room service,
that's gonna get you back in?

966
01:31:00,455 --> 01:31:04,118
That's not the job.
This is the job.

967
01:31:05,860 --> 01:31:09,159
You come up to his head,
you shoot him right above the eye.

968
01:31:09,230 --> 01:31:11,926
Put the gun in his hand,
let it fall.

969
01:31:13,734 --> 01:31:15,998
You got two minutes.

970
01:31:19,106 --> 01:31:21,074
Hey, man, you can't make me
do this.

971
01:31:21,142 --> 01:31:26,011
Hey, I'm not making you do anything.
You turn it down, you turn it down.

972
01:31:26,080 --> 01:31:29,675
You can't handle it,
I handle it.

973
01:32:32,179 --> 01:32:33,612
What?

974
01:32:36,350 --> 01:32:39,285
- Something happened.
- What?

975
01:32:41,822 --> 01:32:43,983
We got a different situation.

976
01:32:45,826 --> 01:32:48,260
I don't even know how to say it.

977
01:33:01,075 --> 01:33:02,508
I see.

978
01:33:04,111 --> 01:33:08,047
Didn't I tell you to run?
I told you to run.

979
01:33:08,115 --> 01:33:10,242
I threw you out of the hotel,
and you came back.

980
01:33:10,318 --> 01:33:12,650
I told you to go.
I told you.

981
01:33:12,720 --> 01:33:16,178
- Why didn't you go?
- I gave my word.

982
01:33:17,925 --> 01:33:22,089
You gave your word.
You gave your word.

983
01:33:22,163 --> 01:33:26,429
- Hey, Jerry!
- Hey, fantastic! You gave your word.

984
01:33:26,500 --> 01:33:28,468
- Hey, Jerry.
- I said I'm gonna do it.

985
01:33:28,536 --> 01:33:31,801
I gave my word.
Everybody gave their goddamn word.

986
01:33:35,610 --> 01:33:37,043
Oh, God.

987
01:33:39,013 --> 01:33:41,208
Hey, what are you gonna do?

988
01:33:41,282 --> 01:33:44,274
What are you gonna do?
You gonna shoot me?

989
01:33:44,352 --> 01:33:46,684
You gonna shoot me?

990
01:33:46,754 --> 01:33:50,781
Shoot yourself, shoot yourself.
You're dead.

991
01:33:53,861 --> 01:33:57,558
Great. Now I'm dead.

992
01:33:57,632 --> 01:34:00,897
You're dead. We're all dead.

993
01:34:09,877 --> 01:34:12,311
You got the keys to the car?

994
01:34:15,583 --> 01:34:18,074
I only...
I just keep...

995
01:34:24,425 --> 01:34:26,859
What? What?

996
01:34:27,928 --> 01:34:30,192
I gotta make a phone call.

997
01:34:30,264 --> 01:34:32,198
What phone call?

998
01:34:37,905 --> 01:34:39,839
What phone call?

999
01:34:41,642 --> 01:34:45,237
Don Giuseppe say,
"If you ever need my friendship..."

1000
01:34:49,150 --> 01:34:51,448
Are you nuts?

1001
01:35:01,662 --> 01:35:05,120
Yes, I make a collect call
to Mr. Joseph Vincent...

1002
01:35:05,199 --> 01:35:07,463
from Gino Gaddo in Chicago.

1003
01:35:07,535 --> 01:35:09,901
- Great.
- Gino Gaddo...

1004
01:35:09,970 --> 01:35:15,237
collect to Mr. Joseph Vincent
at this number, and thank you.

1005
01:35:32,793 --> 01:35:37,730
The defendant, having pled guilty
to murder in the first degree...

1006
01:35:37,798 --> 01:35:41,734
and in the absence
of extenuating circumstances...

1007
01:35:42,970 --> 01:35:46,565
we have no alternative
but to sentence the defendant...

1008
01:35:46,640 --> 01:35:49,336
to the maximum allowed by law.

1009
01:35:49,410 --> 01:35:53,676
The term of imprisonment
of 20 years to life.

1010
01:36:01,922 --> 01:36:04,356
Do you have anything
you want to say?

1011
01:36:06,260 --> 01:36:09,354
The car comes on the corner
at 4:00 p.m.

1012
01:36:09,430 --> 01:36:13,196
I shot the son of a bitch
three times in the heart.

